The icon is made with a thick black line and has a simple design. The back part of the "tail" is slightly wider, whereas the tip of the arrow is curving from one side. The symbol is filled with black.

Heavy Rightwards Arrow is often utilized to denote the direction of movement, wind, flow, or the cardinal direction (east). The icon will come in handy in the design of various diagrams and tables. It is suitable for pointing to an important item on the list, symbolically depicting a transition, transformation, and change in general.

There are other arrows pointing to the right in Unicode, for example, [U:21A6], [U:21FE], [U:21D2]. Choose the most suitable one for your task.